README

This is a git webhook client in rust.

- configure /hook/ as the git hook endpoint
- send commit.
- the application will try to find a project whose name is matching the commit passed in config.json
- it will run the command specified in action and write the stdout and stderr logs in its logs.
-

RUN

- cargo run

TEST

Test a sample commit:

curl -X POST -d @sample.json http://127.0.0.1:5000/hook/

